    caption: [The endocrine system of the pancreas. The pancreas contains both exocrine cells (see Fig. 18–3b), which secrete digestive enzymes in the form of zymogens, and clusters of endocrine cells, the islets of Langerhans. The islets contain (cid:3), (cid:2), and (cid:6) cells (also known as A, B, and D cells, respectively), each cell type secreting a specific peptide hormone. 1],
