  "23-27": (
    caption: [Glucose regulation of insulin secre- tion by pancreatic (cid:2) cells. When the blood glucose level is high, active metabolism of glucose in the (cid:2) cell raises intracellular \[ATP\], closing K(cid:2) channels in the plasma membrane and thus depolarizing the mem- brane. In response to this membrane-depolarization triggered by high \[ATP\], voltage-gated Ca2(cid:2) channels open, allowing Ca2(cid:2) to flow into the cell. (Ca2(cid:2) is also released from the endoplasmic reticulum, in response to the initial elevation of \[Ca2(cid:2)\] in the cytosol.) Cytosolic \[Ca2(cid:2)\] is now high enough to trigger insulin release by exocytosis. The numbered processes are discussed in the text. c23HormonalRegulationAndIntegrationOfMammalianMetabolism.indd Page 954 05/10/12 1:18 PM user-F408 c23HormonalRegulationAndIntegrationOfMammalianMetabolism.indd Page 954 05/10/12 1:18 PM user-F408 /Users/user-F408/Desktop /Users/user-F408/Desktop 954],
