    caption: [Obesity caused by defective leptin production. Both of these mice, which are the same age, have defects in the OB gene. The mouse on the right was injected daily with purified leptin and weighs 35 g. The mouse on the left got no leptin and consequently ate more food and was less active; it weighs 67 g.],
