    caption: [Hypothalamic regulation of food intake and energy expenditure. (a) Role of the hypothalamus in its interaction with adipose tissue. The hypothalamus receives input (leptin) from adipose tissue and responds with neuronal signals to adipocytes. (b) Effects of neuronal stimulation of the adipocyte include activation of protein kinase A, which triggers mobilization of fatty acids from TAG and their uncoupled oxida- tion in mitochondria, generating heat but not ATP. c23HormonalRegulationAndIntegrationOfMammalianMetabolism.indd Page 962 05/10/12 1:18 PM user-F408 c23HormonalRegulationAndIntegrationOfMammalianMetabolism.indd Page 962 05/10/12 1:18 PM user-F408 /Users/user-F408/Desktop /Users/user-F408/Desktop 962],
