  "23-40": (
    caption: [mTORC1 stimulates cell growth and prolifera- tion when adequate nutrition is available. mTORC1 is a Ser/ Thr protein kinase activated by growth factors and metabolites that signal a state of adequate nutrition. By phosphorylating key target proteins, mTORC1 activates energy (ATP and NADPH) production for biosynthesis and stimulates the synthesis of proteins and lipids, allowing cell growth and proliferation. (PPP is pentose phosphate pathway; FA is fatty acids.)],
    path: "../fig/image_place_holder.png"
